Doc: The roles of the parties in reporting information such as positions.

Source.Contents:
/#
   The roles of the parties in reporting information such as positions.
 #/
record FpML5.reporting.ReportingRoles {
  # A reference to the party from whose perspective the position is valued, ie. the owner or holder of the position.
  baseParty : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

  # A reference to the party from whose perspective the position is valued, ie. the owner or holder of the position.
  baseAccount : FpML5.reporting.AccountReference?

  # A reference to the party responsible for reporting trading activities.
  activityProvider : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

  # A reference to the party responsible for reporting the position itself and its constituents.
  positionProvider : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

  # A reference to the party responsible for calculating and reporting the valuations of the positions.
  valuationProvider : FpML5.reporting.PartyReference?

}

baseParty.Doc: A reference to the party from whose perspective the position is valued, ie. the owner or holder of the position.
baseParty.Name: baseParty

baseAccount.Name: baseAccount

positionProvider.Name: positionProvider

valuationProvider.Doc: A reference to the party responsible for calculating and reporting the valuations of the positions.
valuationProvider.Name: valuationProvider
